    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i've been hearing a lot of people say that originalism is kind of just a way for judges to sneak in their own conservative politics under the guise of 'history'. how would a scholar defend against that criticism? like, is there a way to see it as a neutral method rather than just a political tool?",
