      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Defenders argue that originalism is not about injecting politics but about adhering to a fixed, objective standard—the historical understanding of the text. They claim that any interpretation that deviates from the original public meaning is inherently subjective and therefore political. In this view, it is a commitment to textual fidelity, not a partisan agenda.",
      "source": "target",
